    public final class FoldRight<A,B>
extends Object
implements Fn3<java.util.function.BiFunction<? super A,? super B,? extends B>,B,Iterable<A>,B>
    Given an Iterable of As, a starting value B, and a BiFunction<A, B, B>, iteratively accumulate over the Iterable, ultimately returning a final B value. If the Iterable is empty, just return the starting B value. This function is the iterative inverse of FoldLeft, such that foldRight(f, 0, asList(1, 2, 3, 4, 5)) is evaluated as f(f(f(f(f(0, 5), 4), 3), 2), 1).

    For more information, read about Catamorphisms.

    See Also:
    FoldLeft
